SIMPLE: specification
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: specification
<hw>spec`i*fi*ca"tion</hw>
<pr>(sp⟦ecr⟧s`⟦icr⟧*f⟦icr⟧*k⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>sp⟦eacute⟧cification</ets>, LL.
<ets>specificatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of specifying
or determining by a mark or limit; notation of limits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This <qex>specification</qex> or limitation of the question
hinders the disputers from wandering away from the precise point of
inquiry.</q> <rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The designation of particulars; particular mention;
<as>as, the <ex>specification</ex> of a charge against an
officer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A written statement containing a minute description
or enumeration of particulars, as of charges against a public officer,
the terms of a contract, the description of an invention, as in a
patent; also, a single article, item, or particular, an allegation of a
specific act, as in a charge of official misconduct.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A detailed listing or description of the required
properties of some object proposed to be built or bought; -- usually
used in the <pluf>plural</pluf>; <as>as, the building
<ex>specifications</ex> require that it withstand an earthquake of
magnitude 8; the program <ex>specifications</ex> require an option to
change the menus</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Specificness</ent>⟦br⟧
